# Readwise Reader API token. Create yours at https://readwise.io/access_token
#
# The CLIs resolve the token in this order:
#   1. READWISE_TOKEN          — the token value directly in the environment
#   2. READWISE_TOKEN_FILE     — path to a file containing the token
#   3. default file            — ~/.config/readwise-tools/token
#
# Recommended: keep the token in a file OUTSIDE this repo, chmod 600, e.g.
#   mkdir -p ~/.config/readwise-tools
#   printf '%s' 'YOUR_TOKEN' > ~/.config/readwise-tools/token
#   chmod 600 ~/.config/readwise-tools/token
#
# Then you need set nothing here — option 3 is used automatically.
# To override the location instead:
# READWISE_TOKEN_FILE=/absolute/path/to/token
#
# Or (less safe on shared shells) the value directly:
# READWISE_TOKEN=your-token-here
